edu.ncsu.csc216.bbtp.model

Class TestCase

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.Observable
      • edu.ncsu.csc216.bbtp.model.TestCase
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class TestCase
extends java.util.Observable
implements java.io.Serializable
    The TestCase class stores and maintains information about a test case found in a black box test plan. This includes: its ID, its creation date, its description, its expected results, its actual results, its last testing date, test completion status, and passing status.
    Author:
    Brian Morris, Nat Ellis
    See Also:

        public TestCase(java.lang.String id,
                java.lang.String desc,
                TestingType type,
                java.util.Date creation,
                java.lang.String exp,
                boolean tested,
                java.util.Date lastTestDate,
                java.lang.String act,
                boolean pass)
        The constructor for TestCase creates a TestCase Object with the provided parameters and notifies the observers of this TestCase. If any of these parameters are null, an empty String, or invalid as determined by the setter methods, an IllegalArgumentException is thrown.
        Parameters:
        id - the ID of this TestCase
        desc - the description of this TestCase
        type - the TestingType of this TestCase
        creation - the creation date of this TestCase
        exp - the expected results of this TestCase
        tested - the boolean that represents whether or not this TestCase has been tested
        lastTestDate - the last testing date of this TestCase
        act - the actual results of this TestCase
        pass - the boolean that represents whether or not this TestCase has passed testing
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the provided parameters are null, an empty String, or invalid as determined by the setter methods

      • compareTo

        public int compareTo(TestCase input)
        Compares the last testing date of this TestCase to that of the given TestCase. Returns a negative value if the testing data of the provided TestCase is less than the testing date of this TestCase, a positive value if it is greater than the testing date of this TestCase, or 0 if the testing dates are both equal. If the provided TestCase is null, a NullPointerException is thrown.
        Parameters:
        input - the TestCase to compare with this TestCase
        Returns:
        0 if the testing dates of both TestCases are equal, a negative value if the provided TestCase has a testing date smaller than the testing date of this TestCase, or a positive value if the provided TestCase has a testing date greater than the testing date of this TestCase
